
CARGA INCREMENTAL
#################

Anexar dados em um conjunto de dados existente no HDFS

Exercícios de Importação BD Sakila – Carga Incremental
######################################################

PS E:\projetos\docker-bigdata>

PS E:\projetos\docker-bigdata> docker exec -it database bash

################ CRIEI UMA NOVA TABELA NO MYSQL (cp_rental_append_2) SOMENTE COM OS CAMPOS rental_id e rental_date, COM BASE NA TABELA RENTAL

mysql> create table cp_rental_append_2 select rental_id, rental_date from rental;
Query OK, 16044 rows affected (5.96 sec)
Records: 16044  Duplicates: 0  Warnings: 0


mysql> select * from cp_rental_append_2 limit 10;
+-----------+---------------------+
| rental_id | rental_date         |
+-----------+---------------------+
|         1 | 2005-05-24 22:53:30 |
|         2 | 2005-05-24 22:54:33 |
|         3 | 2005-05-24 23:03:39 |
|         4 | 2005-05-24 23:04:41 |
|         5 | 2005-05-24 23:05:21 |
|         6 | 2005-05-24 23:08:07 |
|         7 | 2005-05-24 23:11:53 |
|         8 | 2005-05-24 23:31:46 |
|         9 | 2005-05-25 00:00:40 |
|        10 | 2005-05-25 00:02:21 |
+-----------+---------------------+
10 rows in set (0.00 sec)


################ CRIEI UMA NOVA TABELA NO MYSQL (cp_rental_id_2) COM BASE NA TABELA cp_rental_append_2

mysql> create table cp_rental_id_2 select * from cp_rental_append_2;
Query OK, 16044 rows affected (5.49 sec)
Records: 16044  Duplicates: 0  Warnings: 0

mysql> select * from cp_rental_id_2 limit 10;
+-----------+---------------------+
| rental_id | rental_date         |
+-----------+---------------------+
|         1 | 2005-05-24 22:53:30 |
|         2 | 2005-05-24 22:54:33 |
|         3 | 2005-05-24 23:03:39 |
|         4 | 2005-05-24 23:04:41 |
|         5 | 2005-05-24 23:05:21 |
|         6 | 2005-05-24 23:08:07 |
|         7 | 2005-05-24 23:11:53 |
|         8 | 2005-05-24 23:31:46 |
|         9 | 2005-05-25 00:00:40 |
|        10 | 2005-05-25 00:02:21 |
+-----------+---------------------+
10 rows in set (0.00 sec)


################ CRIEI UMA NOVA TABELA NO MYSQL (cp_rental_date_2) COM BASE NA TABELA cp_rental_append_2

mysql> create table cp_rental_date_2 select * from cp_rental_append_2;
Query OK, 16044 rows affected (3.16 sec)
Records: 16044  Duplicates: 0  Warnings: 0

mysql> select * from cp_rental_date_2 limit 10;
+-----------+---------------------+
| rental_id | rental_date         |
+-----------+---------------------+
|         1 | 2005-05-24 22:53:30 |
|         2 | 2005-05-24 22:54:33 |
|         3 | 2005-05-24 23:03:39 |
|         4 | 2005-05-24 23:04:41 |
|         5 | 2005-05-24 23:05:21 |
|         6 | 2005-05-24 23:08:07 |
|         7 | 2005-05-24 23:11:53 |
|         8 | 2005-05-24 23:31:46 |
|         9 | 2005-05-25 00:00:40 |
|        10 | 2005-05-25 00:02:21 |
+-----------+---------------------+
10 rows in set (0.01 sec)

mysql> ^DBye   ###################### CTRL + D

root@database:/# exit  ###################### CTRL + D

PS E:\projetos\docker-bigdata> docker exec -it namenode bash

############################################################################ REALIZANDO IMPORTAÇÕES COM O SQOOP


########################### IMPORTANDO A TABELA cp_rental_append_2 QUE ESTÁ NO MYSQL PARA O HDFS

root@namenode:/# sqoop import --connect jdbc:mysql://database/sakila --username root --password secret --warehouse-dir /user/hive/warehouse/db_
test3_2 -m 1 --table cp_rental_append_2

root@database:/db-sql/sakila# cat insert_rental.sql  ############################### CONTÉM O SCRIP PARA INSERIR DADOS
use sakila;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS cp_rental_append, cp_rental_date, cp_rental_id;
create table cp_rental_append select rental_id, rental_date from rental;
create table cp_rental_date select * from cp_rental_append;
create table cp_rental_id select * from cp_rental_date;

insert into cp_rental_date_2 values(16048,'2005-08-23 22:30:00');
insert into cp_rental_date_2 values(16049,'2005-08-23 22:40:00');
insert into cp_rental_date_2 values(16050,'2005-08-23 22:52:50');
insert into cp_rental_date_2 values(16051,'2005-08-23 22:54:30');
insert into cp_rental_date_2 values(16052,'2005-08-23 22:55:20');
insert into cp_rental_date_2 values(16054,'2005-08-23 22:57:40');
insert into cp_rental_date_2 values(16053,'2005-08-23 22:56:10');
insert into cp_rental_date_2 values(16055,'2005-08-23 22:59:20');

insert into cp_rental_id_2 values(16048,'2005-08-23 22:30:00');
insert into cp_rental_id_2 values(16049,'2005-08-23 22:40:00');
insert into cp_rental_id_2 values(16050,'2005-08-23 22:52:50');
insert into cp_rental_id_2 values(16051,'2005-08-23 22:54:30');
insert into cp_rental_id_2 values(16052,'2005-08-23 22:55:20');
insert into cp_rental_id_2 values(16054,'2005-08-23 22:57:40');
insert into cp_rental_id_2 values(16053,'2005-08-23 22:56:10');
insert into cp_rental_id_2 values(16055,'2005-08-23 22:59:20');

select * from cp_rental_date ORDER By cp_rental_id_2 DESC limit 10;

select * from cp_rental_id ORDER By cp_rental_date_2 DESC limit 10;

###########################################################################################
